{"questionId":"d7afa874-519b-4f1b-b45f-1c75ea45613b_9","correctAnswer":"70875","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"The equation is $y = 900ax^2$. Use the known data point: $x = 2.75$, $y = 9{,}528.75$. Solve for $a$:<br/>$$9528.75 = 900 \\cdot a \\cdot (2.75)^2 = 6806.25a$$<br/>$$a = \\frac{9528.75}{6806.25} = 1.4$$"},{"title":"Solve","content":"Substitute $a = 1.4$ and $x = 7.50$:<br/>$$y = 900 \\cdot 1.4 \\cdot (7.50)^2 = 900 \\cdot 1.4 \\cdot 56.25 = 70{,}875$$"},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>70875</strong> is correct."}]}